# Heltec NrfTracker v2 – Early Review / Testing Notes

Will update as I continue testing.  

Additional notes and photos:  
https://github.com/Nullvoid3771/Heltec-Projects.-/issues/1  

---

## Overview

I was approached by Heltec Automations to test one of their upcoming (unreleased) products, and I was happy to assist.  

**Important:** This is a pre-release sample unit. Final hardware and features may change before public release.

---

## Q&A

### What is the Heltec NrfTracker v2?

A cost-effective, unlicensed, decentralized LoRa radio that supports:

- LoRa communication  
- Bluetooth  
- GNSS (GPS)  
- Expansion via GPIO for sensors and external hardware  

---

### What makes it different?

Key improvements over similar devices:

- nRF52 MCU (better power efficiency vs ESP32)  
- Increased TX power (22± dBm → 28± dBm)  
- Built-in GNSS (no external module required)  
- Solar charging support  

---

### Screen removal

- Secured with 4 screws  
- Connected via ribbon cable (handle carefully)  
- May need removal for GPIO access/soldering  

---

### Firmware

**Preinstalled:**  
- Meshtastic 2.7.19  

**Supported firmware:**
- Meshtastic → https://flasher.meshtastic.org/  
- Meshcore → https://flasher.meshcore.co.uk/  

---

### LoRaWAN / official firmware?

Currently only Meshtastic and Meshcore are officially supported.

---

### Range expectations

Highly dependent on:

- Mesh density (hops)  
- Preset (LongFast, etc.)  
- Elevation / line of sight  
- Antenna quality and tuning  
- RF noise / environment  

**Realistic use case (no hops):**
- ~2 km → 10+ km  

---

### GNSS antenna

- Built-in antenna included  
- Optional external antenna via IPEX  
- Requires hardware mod (0-ohm resistor bridge)  

---

### Real-time tracking use?

Situational.

Best described as:
> A fallback / last-resort tracking solution

Works best:
- Within ~5 km  
- With multiple nodes  
- With good LOS and antenna setup  

---

### Update behavior

- Infrequent updates may appear as “location jumps”  
- Nodes still transmit's location even if not immediately visible.  

---

### Meshtastic settings used for testing. More agressive configurations could be used for Real-Time Tracking. 

- Role: Tracker  
- Broadcast interval: 900s  
- GPS update: 60s  
- Smart Positioning: Disabled  

Docs:  
https://meshtastic.org/docs/configuration/radio/device/  
https://meshtastic.org/docs/configuration/radio/position/  

